Credit Suisse, Actelion, Swisscom, UBS: Swiss Equity Preview

-- B y   L e i g h   B a l d w i n
-- 
2011-02-21T07:50:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-21/credit-suisse-actelion-and-swisscom-swiss-equity-preview.html
The following companies’ shares may
be active in Zurich. Stock symbols are in parentheses after
company names. Share prices are from the last close.  The  Swiss Market Index  of the biggest and most actively
traded companies increased 0.2 percent to 6,717.25.  Actelion Ltd. (ATLN VX): The Swiss drugmaker may be able to
secure its fortunes for the next two decades if products under
development were tested successfully in 2011, Chief Executive
Officer Jean-Paul Clozel told SonntagsZeitung. The stock fell
1.6 percent to 52.7 Swiss francs.    Credit Suisse Group AG  (CSGN VX): Koor Industries Ltd., the
holding company controlled by Nochi Dankner that holds about 3.1
percent of Credit Suisse, said the Swiss bank reported a $2
billion issuance of capital notes, according to a statement
filed with the Tel Aviv Stock Exchange. The stock rose 0.8
percent to 44.99 francs.        Kudelski SA  (KUD SW): Shares in the manufacturer of digital
security products were cut to “underperform” from “neutral”
at Exane BNP Paribas. The shares fell 1.8 percent to 21.7
francs.    Swisscom AG  (SCMN VX): Switzerland’s largest phone company
would have waited longer before acquiring Fastweb SpA if it had
known Italy’s second-largest fixed line provider was in such a
“muddle,” Swisscom President Anton Scherrer told
SonntagsZeitung in an interview. The stock fell 0.3 percent to
415.1 francs.        UBS AG  (UBSN VX): Shares in the bank were raised to “buy”
from “neutral” at Goldman Sachs Group Inc. The shares rose 1
percent to 18.93 francs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
